The paper deals with the efficient computation of PageRank and personalized PageRank on large-scale dynamically evolving social networks, which involves algorithms and data structures for handling large graphs, distributed computing, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), and cs.DB (Databases).
